  "riddle": "1. Seek the page where the company behind ubiquitous plastic payment methods began its journey. In what year was it established?\n\n2. Once you have discovered the founding year, sum its digits to find your next answer.\n\n3. Venture to the page that explores the sector of card transactions. How many different types of cards are mentioned in the opening?\n\n4. For the number you found, convert it to a Roman numeral. How many characters does it take to write that numeral?\n\n5. Navigate over to the entry that reveals details about machines dispensing cash. Count the top-level sections present in the table of contents there.\n\n6. Now, uncover the city that serves as the headquarters of a well-known grocery chain noted for its organic foods. What is the name of this city?\n\n7. An exploration of Austin, Texas awaits — how high does this city rise above sea level?\n\n8. Nearby, how many hospitals can you count that cater to the needs of its residents?\n\n9. Reveal the difference between the elevation you discovered in clue 7 and the count of hospitals gathered in clue 8.\n\n10. From the name of the grocery chain you uncovered, how many vowels can you discover?\n\n11. Journey to the article that discussions the vast online marketplace; how many languages is it accessible in?\n\n12. In your travels, how populous is the land of Ireland?\n\n13. Now direct your gaze to the topic of legal frameworks in Europe. How many subsections are found within the section discussing mergers and abuse of dominance?\n\n14. Shift your attention to the capital of Russia and determine its height above sea level.\n\n15. Seek out the geographical coordinates that pinpoint a city in California known for its close ties to Silicon Valley.\n\n16. To conclude your quest, compute the result of the following: (clue 3 + clue 4 + clue 5 + clue 7) modulo 10. The answer will yield a single digit (0-9).",
